  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I'm testing a higher than usual load of transactions, and discovered a bottleneck in the RemoveTx function. It simply traverses all accounts in the queue\nfor address, txs := range pool.queue {\n}\nand removes the hash when found. The performance of this algorithm is really bad when there 50 account and 20k-50k transactions, and it's getting worse exponentially with increase of transactions/addresses.\n\nPlease consider rewriting this function using some kind of reverse map hash->address and access the required address directly without scanning the whole queue.\n",
